<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: NESICIDE = DLL HELL!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12474&amp;p=142789#p142789"><![CDATA[
A lot of people seem to have the privilege to run executables from removable media but not to install to the hard disk. And when you &quot;install&quot; a program, an uninstall entry gets written to the table used by Programs and Features &gt; Change or Remove Programs.<br /><br />But there are a few things for which you do need an installer (at least on Windows), such as the ability to shell execute a project file (that is, double-click it in File Explorer and expect it to open in the correct program).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Mar 11, 2015 7:37 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
